name: Benton Franklin - Kennewick COVID Vaccine Clinic
info: ********************JOHNSON and JOHNSON*************************** Now Johnson and Johnson ** Must be 18 years of age or over. Please do not come if you are feeling ill. Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location you must either live or work in Washington state. If you do not live or work in Washington, please do not make an appointment or travel to this site.**Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided. Follow posted signage about traffic and parking at the site. **Enter the fairgrounds from 10th Street.**

name: Community Vaccination Center at Bellingham Technical College
address: Bellingham Technical College, 3028 Lindbergh Avenue – Building G, Bellingham WA, 98225
info: We are currently vaccinating eligible individuals as determined by Washington State Department of Health ages 18 and older.  If appointments are full, you can click on “Waiting List” to register yourself for standby appointments for that scheduling day only.  If there are extra doses of vaccine at the end of the day, individuals on the waiting list will be called in scheduling order.  You can also make an appointment by calling 360-778-6075 Monday through Friday from 8:30 AM to 4:00 PM.  Phone appointments are available for people who do not have an email, internet access, need interpretation services, or are having difficulty navigating the site.  On-site registration is available as well. Masks must be worn at all times at the site and six-foot distancing will be maintained.  The site is ADA accessible.  For directions, visit www.vaccinatewhatcom.org.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Thurston County Fairgrounds 2705 Carpenter Rd SE, Olympia 98503, Lacey WA, 98503
info:
This is a Moderna 2nd dose vaccination event for anyone age 18 and older. 

• This is a drive thru clinic held at Thurston County Fairgrounds, 2705 Carpenter Rd SE, Olympia 98503. The clinic time is 8:00AM - 5:00PM. After you register, you can show up at any time during the clinic to be vaccinated. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it.• Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers, if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
